{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm here today representing a team of artists and technologists and filmmakers"},{"time":5000,"text":"that worked together on a remarkable film project for the last four years."},{"time":8000,"text":"And along the way they created a breakthrough in computer visualization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12000,"text":"So I want to show you a clip of the film now."},{"time":15000,"text":"Hopefully it won't stutter."},{"time":18000,"text":"And if we did our jobs well, you won't know that we were even involved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"Voice (Video): I don't know how it's possible ..."},{"time":24000,"text":"but you seem to have more hair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"Brad Pitt: What if I told you that I wasn't getting older ..."},{"time":30000,"text":"but I was getting younger than everybody else?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"I was born with some form of disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"Voice: What kind of disease?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"BP: I was born old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"Man: I'm sorry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"BP: No need to be. There's nothing wrong with old age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"Girl: Are you sick?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52000,"text":"BP: I heard momma and Tizzy whisper,"},{"time":55000,"text":"and they said I was gonna die soon."},{"time":57000,"text":"But ... maybe not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"Girl: You're different than anybody I've ever met."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"BB: There were many changes ..."},{"time":67000,"text":"some you could see, some you couldn't."},{"time":70000,"text":"Hair started growing in all sorts of places,"},{"time":73000,"text":"along with other things."},{"time":76000,"text":"I felt pretty good, considering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"Ed Ulbrich: That was a clip from \"The Curious Case of Benjamin Button.\""},{"time":84000,"text":"Many of you, maybe you've seen it or you've heard of the story,"},{"time":88000,"text":"but what you might not know"},{"time":90000,"text":"is that for nearly the first hour of the film,"},{"time":92000,"text":"the main character, Benjamin Button, who's played by Brad Pitt,"},{"time":95000,"text":"is completely computer-generated from the neck up."},{"time":98000,"text":"Now, there's no use of prosthetic makeup"},{"time":101000,"text":"or photography of Brad superimposed over another actor's body."},{"time":104000,"text":"We've created a completely digital human head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107000,"text":"So I'd like to start with a little bit of history on the project."},{"time":110000,"text":"This is based on an F. Scott Fitzgerald short story."},{"time":112000,"text":"It's about a man who's born old and lives his life in reverse."},{"time":115000,"text":"Now, this movie has floated around Hollywood"},{"time":117000,"text":"for well over half a century,"},{"time":119000,"text":"and we first got involved with the project in the early '90s,"},{"time":122000,"text":"with Ron Howard as the director."},{"time":124000,"text":"We took a lot of meetings and we seriously considered it."},{"time":127000,"text":"But at the time we had to throw in the towel."},{"time":129000,"text":"It was deemed impossible."},{"time":131000,"text":"It was beyond the technology of the day to depict a man aging backwards."},{"time":135000,"text":"The human form, in particular the human head,"},{"time":138000,"text":"has been considered the Holy Grail of our industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"The project came back to us about a decade later,"},{"time":144000,"text":"and this time with a director named David Fincher."},{"time":147000,"text":"Now, Fincher is an interesting guy."},{"time":150000,"text":"David is fearless of technology,"},{"time":152000,"text":"and he is absolutely tenacious."},{"time":154000,"text":"And David won't take \"no.\""},{"time":156000,"text":"And David believed, like we do in the visual effects industry,"},{"time":159000,"text":"that anything is possible"},{"time":162000,"text":"as long as you have enough time, resources and, of course, money.\n"},{"time":165000,"text":"And so David had an interesting take on the film,"},{"time":169000,"text":"and he threw a challenge at us."},{"time":172000,"text":"He wanted the main character of the film to be played"},{"time":175000,"text":"from the cradle to the grave by one actor."},{"time":177000,"text":"It happened to be this guy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"We went through a process of elimination and a process of discovery"},{"time":182000,"text":"with David, and we ruled out, of course, swapping actors."},{"time":185000,"text":"That was one idea: that we would have different actors,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and we would hand off from actor to actor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"We even ruled out the idea of using makeup."},{"time":192000,"text":"We realized that prosthetic makeup just wouldn't hold up,"},{"time":195000,"text":"particularly in close-up."},{"time":197000,"text":"And makeup is an additive process. You have to build the face up."},{"time":200000,"text":"And David wanted to carve deeply into Brad's face"},{"time":203000,"text":"to bring the aging to this character."},{"time":205000,"text":"He needed to be a very sympathetic character."},{"time":207000,"text":"So we decided to cast a series of little people"},{"time":210000,"text":"that would play the different bodies of Benjamin"},{"time":213000,"text":"at the different increments of his life"},{"time":215000,"text":"and that we would in fact create a computer-generated version of Brad's head,"},{"time":218000,"text":"aged to appear as Benjamin,"},{"time":220000,"text":"and attach that to the body of the real actor."},{"time":223000,"text":"Sounded great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225000,"text":"Of course, this was the Holy Grail of our industry,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and the fact that this guy is a global icon didn't help either,"},{"time":231000,"text":"because I'm sure if any of you ever stand in line at the grocery store,"},{"time":234000,"text":"you know -- we see his face constantly."},{"time":237000,"text":"So there really was no tolerable margin of error."},{"time":239000,"text":"There were two studios involved: Warner Brothers and Paramount."},{"time":242000,"text":"And they both believed this would make an amazing film, of course,"},{"time":245000,"text":"but it was a very high-risk proposition."},{"time":248000,"text":"There was lots of money and reputations at stake."},{"time":251000,"text":"But we believed that we had a very solid methodology"},{"time":254000,"text":"that might work ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257000,"text":"But despite our verbal assurances,"},{"time":260000,"text":"they wanted some proof."},{"time":262000,"text":"And so, in 2004, they commissioned us to do a screen test of Benjamin."},{"time":265000,"text":"And we did it in about five weeks."},{"time":268000,"text":"But we used lots of cheats and shortcuts."},{"time":271000,"text":"We basically put something together to get through the meeting."},{"time":274000,"text":"I'll roll that for you now. This was the first test for Benjamin Button."},{"time":277000,"text":"And in here, you can see, that's a computer-generated head --"},{"time":280000,"text":"pretty good -- attached to the body of an actor."},{"time":283000,"text":"And it worked. And it gave the studio great relief."},{"time":286000,"text":"After many years of starts and stops on this project,"},{"time":289000,"text":"and making that tough decision,"},{"time":292000,"text":"they finally decided to greenlight the movie."},{"time":295000,"text":"And I can remember, actually, when I got the phone call to congratulate us,"},{"time":298000,"text":"to say the movie was a go,"},{"time":300000,"text":"I actually threw up."},{"time":302000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":304000,"text":"You know, this is some tough stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"So we started to have early team meetings,"},{"time":309000,"text":"and we got everybody together,"},{"time":311000,"text":"and it was really more like therapy in the beginning,"},{"time":314000,"text":"convincing each other and reassuring each other that we could actually undertake this."},{"time":317000,"text":"We had to hold up an hour of a movie with a character."},{"time":320000,"text":"And it's not a special effects film; it has to be a man."},{"time":323000,"text":"We really felt like we were in a -- kind of a 12-step program."},{"time":326000,"text":"And of course, the first step is: admit you've got a problem. (Laughter)"},{"time":330000,"text":"So we had a big problem:"},{"time":332000,"text":"we didn't know how we were going to do this."},{"time":335000,"text":"But we did know one thing."},{"time":337000,"text":"Being from the visual effects industry,"},{"time":340000,"text":"we, with David, believed that we now had enough time,"},{"time":343000,"text":"enough resources, and, God, we hoped we had enough money."},{"time":346000,"text":"And we had enough passion to will the processes and technology into existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"So, when you're faced with something like that,"},{"time":353000,"text":"of course you've got to break it down."},{"time":355000,"text":"You take the big problem and you break it down into smaller pieces"},{"time":357000,"text":"and you start to attack that."},{"time":358000,"text":"So we had three main areas that we had to focus on."},{"time":360000,"text":"We needed to make Brad look a lot older --"},{"time":362000,"text":"needed to age him 45 years or so."},{"time":364000,"text":"And we also needed to make sure that we could take Brad's idiosyncrasies,"},{"time":370000,"text":"his little tics, the little subtleties that make him who he is"},{"time":372000,"text":"and have that translate through our process"},{"time":374000,"text":"so that it appears in Benjamin on the screen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"And we also needed to create a character"},{"time":379000,"text":"that could hold up under, really, all conditions."},{"time":382000,"text":"He needed to be able to walk in broad daylight,"},{"time":384000,"text":"at nighttime, under candlelight,"},{"time":387000,"text":"he had to hold an extreme close-up,"},{"time":389000,"text":"he had to deliver dialogue,"},{"time":390000,"text":"he had to be able to run, he had to be able to sweat,"},{"time":392000,"text":"he had to be able to take a bath, to cry,"},{"time":394000,"text":"he even had to throw up."},{"time":395000,"text":"Not all at the same time --"},{"time":396000,"text":"but he had to, you know, do all of those things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398000,"text":"And the work had to hold up for almost the first hour of the movie."},{"time":401000,"text":"We did about 325 shots."},{"time":403000,"text":"So we needed a system that would allow Benjamin"},{"time":406000,"text":"to do everything a human being can do."},{"time":409000,"text":"And we realized that there was a giant chasm"},{"time":412000,"text":"between the state of the art of technology in 2004"},{"time":415000,"text":"and where we needed it to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"So we focused on motion capture."},{"time":420000,"text":"I'm sure many of you have seen motion capture."},{"time":422000,"text":"The state of the art at the time"},{"time":424000,"text":"was something called marker-based motion capture."},{"time":426000,"text":"I'll give you an example here."},{"time":427000,"text":"It's basically the idea of, you wear a leotard,"},{"time":429000,"text":"and they put some reflective markers on your body,"},{"time":431000,"text":"and instead of using cameras,"},{"time":433000,"text":"there're infrared sensors around a volume,"},{"time":435000,"text":"and those infrared sensors track the three-dimensional position"},{"time":437000,"text":"of those markers in real time."},{"time":439000,"text":"And then animators can take the data of the motion of those markers"},{"time":442000,"text":"and apply them to a computer-generated character."},{"time":444000,"text":"You can see the computer characters on the right"},{"time":447000,"text":"are having the same complex motion as the dancers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450000,"text":"But we also looked at numbers of other films at the time"},{"time":452000,"text":"that were using facial marker tracking,"},{"time":454000,"text":"and that's the idea of putting markers on the human face"},{"time":456000,"text":"and doing the same process."},{"time":457000,"text":"And as you can see, it gives you a pretty crappy performance."},{"time":461000,"text":"That's not terribly compelling."},{"time":464000,"text":"And what we realized"},{"time":466000,"text":"was that what we needed"},{"time":467000,"text":"was the information that was going on between the markers."},{"time":469000,"text":"We needed the subtleties of the skin."},{"time":472000,"text":"We needed to see skin moving over muscle moving over bone."},{"time":475000,"text":"We needed creases and dimples and wrinkles and all of those things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477000,"text":"Our first revelation was to completely abort and walk away from"},{"time":480000,"text":"the technology of the day, the status quo, the state of the art."},{"time":483000,"text":"So we aborted using motion capture."},{"time":486000,"text":"And we were now well out of our comfort zone,"},{"time":489000,"text":"and in uncharted territory."},{"time":491000,"text":"So we were left with this idea"},{"time":494000,"text":"that we ended up calling \"technology stew.\""},{"time":497000,"text":"We started to look out in other fields."},{"time":499000,"text":"The idea was that we were going to find"},{"time":502000,"text":"nuggets or gems of technology"},{"time":504000,"text":"that come from other industries like medical imaging,"},{"time":506000,"text":"the video game space,"},{"time":507000,"text":"and re-appropriate them."},{"time":509000,"text":"And we had to create kind of a sauce."},{"time":512000,"text":"And the sauce was code in software"},{"time":515000,"text":"that we'd written to allow these disparate pieces of technology"},{"time":518000,"text":"to come together and work as one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"Initially, we came across some remarkable research"},{"time":522000,"text":"done by a gentleman named Dr. Paul Ekman in the early '70s."},{"time":525000,"text":"He believed that he could, in fact,"},{"time":528000,"text":"catalog the human face."},{"time":530000,"text":"And he came up with this idea of Facial Action Coding System, or FACS."},{"time":533000,"text":"He believed that there were 70 basic poses"},{"time":536000,"text":"or shapes of the human face,"},{"time":539000,"text":"and that those basic poses or shapes of the face"},{"time":542000,"text":"can be combined to create infinite possibilities"},{"time":545000,"text":"of everything the human face is capable of doing."},{"time":547000,"text":"And of course, these transcend age, race, culture, gender."},{"time":550000,"text":"So this became the foundation of our research as we went forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554000,"text":"And then we came across some remarkable technology"},{"time":557000,"text":"called Contour."},{"time":558000,"text":"And here you can see a subject having phosphorus makeup"},{"time":561000,"text":"stippled on her face."},{"time":563000,"text":"And now what we're looking at is really creating a surface capture"},{"time":566000,"text":"as opposed to a marker capture."},{"time":568000,"text":"The subject stands in front of a computer array of cameras,"},{"time":570000,"text":"and those cameras can, frame-by-frame,"},{"time":572000,"text":"reconstruct the geometry of exactly what the subject's doing at the moment."},{"time":575000,"text":"So, effectively, you get 3D data in real time of the subject."},{"time":580000,"text":"And if you look in a comparison,"},{"time":583000,"text":"on the left, we see what volumetric data gives us"},{"time":586000,"text":"and on the right you see what markers give us."},{"time":589000,"text":"So, clearly, we were in a substantially better place for this."},{"time":591000,"text":"But these were the early days of this technology,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and it wasn't really proven yet."},{"time":595000,"text":"We measure complexity and fidelity of data"},{"time":597000,"text":"in terms of polygonal count."},{"time":599000,"text":"And so, on the left, we were seeing 100,000 polygons."},{"time":602000,"text":"We could go up into the millions of polygons."},{"time":604000,"text":"It seemed to be infinite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606000,"text":"This was when we had our \"Aha!\""},{"time":608000,"text":"This was the breakthrough."},{"time":609000,"text":"This is when we're like, \"OK, we're going to be OK,"},{"time":611000,"text":"This is actually going to work.\""},{"time":612000,"text":"And the \"Aha!\" was, what if we could take Brad Pitt,"},{"time":616000,"text":"and we could put Brad in this device,"},{"time":619000,"text":"and use this Contour process,"},{"time":621000,"text":"and we could stipple on this phosphorescent makeup"},{"time":623000,"text":"and put him under the black lights,"},{"time":624000,"text":"and we could, in fact, scan him in real time"},{"time":627000,"text":"performing Ekman's FACS poses."},{"time":629000,"text":"Right? So, effectively,"},{"time":631000,"text":"we ended up with a 3D database"},{"time":633000,"text":"of everything Brad Pitt's face is capable of doing."},{"time":636000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"From there, we actually carved up those faces"},{"time":641000,"text":"into smaller pieces and components of his face."},{"time":644000,"text":"So we ended up with literally thousands and thousands and thousands of shapes,"},{"time":647000,"text":"a complete database of all possibilities"},{"time":650000,"text":"that his face is capable of doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653000,"text":"Now, that's great, except we had him at age 44."},{"time":656000,"text":"We need to put another 40 years on him at this point."},{"time":659000,"text":"We brought in Rick Baker,"},{"time":661000,"text":"and Rick is one of the great makeup and special effects gurus"},{"time":663000,"text":"of our industry."},{"time":664000,"text":"And we also brought in a gentleman named Kazu Tsuji,"},{"time":667000,"text":"and Kazu Tsuji is one of the great photorealist sculptors of our time."},{"time":670000,"text":"And we commissioned them to make a maquette,"},{"time":673000,"text":"or a bust, of Benjamin."},{"time":675000,"text":"So, in the spirit of \"The Great Unveiling\" -- I had to do this --"},{"time":678000,"text":"I had to unveil something."},{"time":680000,"text":"So this is Ben 80."},{"time":682000,"text":"We created three of these:"},{"time":684000,"text":"there's Ben 80, there's Ben 70, there's Ben 60."},{"time":686000,"text":"And this really became the template for moving forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689000,"text":"Now, this was made from a life cast of Brad."},{"time":691000,"text":"So, in fact, anatomically, it is correct."},{"time":694000,"text":"The eyes, the jaw, the teeth:"},{"time":697000,"text":"everything is in perfect alignment with what the real guy has."},{"time":700000,"text":"We have these maquettes scanned into the computer"},{"time":702000,"text":"at very high resolution --"},{"time":704000,"text":"enormous polygonal count."},{"time":706000,"text":"And so now we had three age increments of Benjamin"},{"time":710000,"text":"in the computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712000,"text":"But we needed to get a database of him doing more than that."},{"time":715000,"text":"We went through this process, then, called retargeting."},{"time":718000,"text":"This is Brad doing one of the Ekman FACS poses."},{"time":720000,"text":"And here's the resulting data that comes from that,"},{"time":723000,"text":"the model that comes from that."},{"time":725000,"text":"Retargeting is the process of transposing that data"},{"time":728000,"text":"onto another model."},{"time":730000,"text":"And because the life cast, or the bust -- the maquette -- of Benjamin"},{"time":733000,"text":"was made from Brad,"},{"time":735000,"text":"we could transpose the data of Brad at 44"},{"time":738000,"text":"onto Brad at 87."},{"time":740000,"text":"So now, we had a 3D database of everything Brad Pitt's face can do"},{"time":743000,"text":"at age 87, in his 70s and in his 60s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"Next we had to go into the shooting process."},{"time":750000,"text":"So while all that's going on,"},{"time":751000,"text":"we're down in New Orleans and locations around the world."},{"time":753000,"text":"And we shot our body actors,"},{"time":755000,"text":"and we shot them wearing blue hoods."},{"time":757000,"text":"So these are the gentleman who played Benjamin."},{"time":759000,"text":"And the blue hoods helped us with two things:"},{"time":761000,"text":"one, we could easily erase their heads;"},{"time":763000,"text":"and we also put tracking markers on their heads"},{"time":765000,"text":"so we could recreate the camera motion"},{"time":767000,"text":"and the lens optics from the set."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"But now we needed to get Brad's performance to drive our virtual Benjamin."},{"time":772000,"text":"And so we edited the footage that was shot on location"},{"time":774000,"text":"with the rest of the cast and the body actors"},{"time":777000,"text":"and about six months later"},{"time":779000,"text":"we brought Brad onto a sound stage in Los Angeles"},{"time":782000,"text":"and he watched on the screen."},{"time":785000,"text":"His job, then, was to become Benjamin."},{"time":787000,"text":"And so we looped the scenes."},{"time":788000,"text":"He watched again and again."},{"time":789000,"text":"We encouraged him to improvise."},{"time":791000,"text":"And he took Benjamin into interesting and unusual places"},{"time":794000,"text":"that we didn't think he was going to go."},{"time":796000,"text":"We shot him with four HD cameras"},{"time":798000,"text":"so we'd get multiple views of him"},{"time":799000,"text":"and then David would choose the take of Brad being Benjamin"},{"time":802000,"text":"that he thought best matched the footage"},{"time":805000,"text":"with the rest of the cast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"From there we went into a process called image analysis."},{"time":809000,"text":"And so here, you can see again, the chosen take."},{"time":812000,"text":"And you are seeing, now, that data being transposed on to Ben 87."},{"time":815000,"text":"And so, what's interesting about this is"},{"time":818000,"text":"we used something called image analysis,"},{"time":820000,"text":"which is taking timings from different components of Benjamin's face."},{"time":823000,"text":"And so we could choose, say, his left eyebrow."},{"time":826000,"text":"And the software would tell us that, well,"},{"time":828000,"text":"in frame 14 the left eyebrow begins to move from here to here,"},{"time":830000,"text":"and it concludes moving in frame 32."},{"time":832000,"text":"And so we could choose numbers of positions on the face"},{"time":834000,"text":"to pull that data from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836000,"text":"And then, the sauce I talked about with our technology stew --"},{"time":838000,"text":"that secret sauce was, effectively, software that allowed us to"},{"time":841000,"text":"match the performance footage of Brad"},{"time":844000,"text":"in live action with our database of aged Benjamin,"},{"time":848000,"text":"the FACS shapes that we had."},{"time":850000,"text":"On a frame-by-frame basis,"},{"time":853000,"text":"we could actually reconstruct a 3D head"},{"time":856000,"text":"that exactly matched the performance of Brad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859000,"text":"So this was how the finished shot appeared in the film."},{"time":862000,"text":"And here you can see the body actor."},{"time":864000,"text":"And then this is what we called the \"dead head,\" no reference to Jerry Garcia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867000,"text":"And then here's the reconstructed performance"},{"time":870000,"text":"now with the timings of the performance."},{"time":873000,"text":"And then, again, the final shot."},{"time":876000,"text":"It was a long process."},{"time":878000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":889000,"text":"The next section here, I'm going to just blast through this,"},{"time":891000,"text":"because we could do a whole TEDTalk on the next several slides."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895000,"text":"We had to create a lighting system."},{"time":898000,"text":"So really, a big part of our processes was creating a lighting environment"},{"time":901000,"text":"for every single location that Benjamin had to appear"},{"time":903000,"text":"so that we could put Ben's head into any scene"},{"time":906000,"text":"and it would exactly match the lighting that's on the other actors"},{"time":909000,"text":"in the real world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910000,"text":"We also had to create an eye system."},{"time":913000,"text":"We found the old adage, you know,"},{"time":915000,"text":"\"The eyes are the window to the soul,\""},{"time":917000,"text":"absolutely true."},{"time":918000,"text":"So the key here was to keep everybody looking in Ben's eyes."},{"time":920000,"text":"And if you could feel the warmth, and feel the humanity,"},{"time":922000,"text":"and feel his intent coming through the eyes,"},{"time":925000,"text":"then we would succeed."},{"time":926000,"text":"So we had one person focused on the eye system"},{"time":929000,"text":"for almost two full years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"We also had to create a mouth system."},{"time":933000,"text":"We worked from dental molds of Brad."},{"time":935000,"text":"We had to age the teeth over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937000,"text":"We also had to create an articulating tongue that allowed him to enunciate his words."},{"time":940000,"text":"There was a whole system written in software to articulate the tongue."},{"time":942000,"text":"We had one person devoted to the tongue for about nine months."},{"time":944000,"text":"He was very popular."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946000,"text":"Skin displacement: another big deal."},{"time":949000,"text":"The skin had to be absolutely accurate."},{"time":951000,"text":"He's also in an old age home, he's in a nursing home"},{"time":954000,"text":"around other old people,"},{"time":956000,"text":"so he had to look exactly the same as the others."},{"time":958000,"text":"So, lots of work on skin deformation,"},{"time":959000,"text":"you can see in some of these cases it works,"},{"time":960000,"text":"in some cases it looks bad."},{"time":961000,"text":"This is a very, very, very early test in our process."},{"time":963000,"text":"So, effectively we created a digital puppet"},{"time":966000,"text":"that Brad Pitt could operate with his own face."},{"time":969000,"text":"There were no animators necessary to come in and interpret behavior"},{"time":973000,"text":"or enhance his performance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975000,"text":"There was something that we encountered, though,"},{"time":978000,"text":"that we ended up calling \"the digital Botox effect.\""},{"time":981000,"text":"So, as things went through this process,"},{"time":984000,"text":"Fincher would always say, \"It sandblasts the edges off of the performance.\""},{"time":987000,"text":"And thing our process and the technology couldn't do,"},{"time":990000,"text":"is they couldn't understand intent,"},{"time":993000,"text":"the intent of the actor."},{"time":995000,"text":"So it sees a smile as a smile."},{"time":997000,"text":"It doesn't recognize an ironic smile, or a happy smile,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"or a frustrated smile."},{"time":1001000,"text":"So it did take humans to kind of push it one way or another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004000,"text":"But we ended up calling the entire process"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and all the technology \"emotion capture,\""},{"time":1009000,"text":"as opposed to just motion capture."},{"time":1010000,"text":"Take another look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1013000,"text":"Brad Pitt: Well, I heard momma and Tizzy whisper,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"and they said I was gonna die soon,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"but ... maybe not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039000,"text":"EU: That's how to create a digital human in 18 minutes."},{"time":1042000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050000,"text":"A couple of quick factoids;"},{"time":1052000,"text":"it really took 155 people over two years,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"and we didn't even talk about 60 hairstyles and an all-digital haircut."},{"time":1060000,"text":"But, that is Benjamin. Thank you."}]}]}